description: The integer values of x/d(x) in order of magnitude of x in A033950.
links: Nathaniel Johnston, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
example: If n=63, then x=625 and d(x) = 5 divides x. The quotient is 125 = a(63).
maple: with(numtheory): A033950 := proc(n) option remember: local k: if(n=1)then return 1: else k:=procname(n-1)+1: do if(type(k/tau(k),integer))then return k: fi: k:=k+1: od: fi: end: A036762 := proc(n) return A033950(n)/tau(A033950(n)): end: seq(A036762(n),n=1..70); # Nathaniel Johnston, May 04 2011
author: _Labos Elemer_
